                                "stop": 11.632,
                                "byte_start": 85377,
                                "byte_stop": 131979,
                                "text": "01-653, Federal Communications Commission versus Nextwave Personal Communications and a companion case will be announced by Justice Scalia."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.632,
                        "stop": 344.529,
                        "byte_start": 131979,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.632,
                                "stop": 18.605,
                                "byte_start": 131979,
                                "byte_stop": 159878,
                                "text": "These cases come to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.605,
                                "stop": 31.89,
                                "byte_start": 159878,
                                "byte_stop": 212959,
                                "text": "The Federal Communications Commission awarded Spectrum Licenses to Nextwave Personal Communications and allowed Nextwave to pay for these licenses in installments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.89,
                                "stop": 40.921,
                                "byte_start": 212959,
                                "byte_stop": 249113,
                                "text": "The company subsequently filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy and suspended payments to all creditors including the FCC."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.921,
                                "stop": 56,
                                "byte_start": 249113,
                                "byte_stop": 309403,
                                "text": "Its plan of reorganization envisioned repayment of its obligations to the FCC but the FCC objected to the plan asserting that Nextwave\u0027s licenses had been cancelled automatically when the company missed its payment deadline."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56,
                                "stop": 72.353,
                                "byte_start": 309403,
                                "byte_stop": 374814,
                                "text": "Nextwave filed a petition with the FCC seeking reconsideration of the license cancellation and upon denial appealed to the D.C. Circuit asserting that the cancellation violated the Bankruptcy Act and thus should be set aside under the Administrative Procedure Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.353,
                                "stop": 78.675,
                                "byte_start": 374814,
                                "byte_stop": 400100,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals agreed, we granted certiorari and we now affirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.675,
                                "stop": 85.184,
                                "byte_start": 400100,
                                "byte_stop": 426118,
                                "text": "The Administrative Procedure Act requires Federal Courts to set aside Federal Agency action that is not in accordance with law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.184,
                                "stop": 109.189,
                                "byte_start": 426118,
                                "byte_stop": 522144,
                                "text": "The question before us is whether the FCCs cancellation violated Section 525 of the Bankruptcy Act which provides in relevant part that \u201ca governmental unit may not revoke a license to person that is a debtor under this Title, solely because such debtor has not paid a debt that is dischargeable\u201d in bankruptcy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.189,
                                "stop": 117.043,
                                "byte_start": 522144,
                                "byte_stop": 553596,
                                "text": "Here the proximate cause for the FCC\u2019s revocation of the licenses was not Nextwave\u2019s failure to make the payments that were due."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.043,
                                "stop": 120.429,
                                "byte_start": 553596,
                                "byte_stop": 567179,
                                "text": "That suffices to invoke Section 525."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.429,
                                "stop": 130.323,
                                "byte_start": 567179,
                                "byte_stop": 606677,
                                "text": "Contrary to petitioner\u2019s contention, it makes no difference whether the agency has some regulatory motive behind its action in canceling for nonpayment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.323,
                                "stop": 160.593,
                                "byte_start": 606677,
                                "byte_stop": 727780,
                                "text": "When the statute refers to failure to pay a debt as the sole cause of cancellation, it cannot reasonably be understood to include among the other causes whose presence can preclude application of the prohibition, the government unit\u2019s motive in adopting a cancellation for nonpayment rule such a reading would deprive Section 525 of all force since it is hard to imagine a situation in which a governmental unit would not have some further motive behind the rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.593,
                                "stop": 174.634,
                                "byte_start": 727780,
                                "byte_stop": 783996,
                                "text": "Petitioner\u2019s contend that Nextwave\u2019s license obligations to the Commission are not \u201cwithin the meaning of 525 debts that are dischargeable in bankruptcy\u0022 because they function as regulatory conditions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.634,
                                "stop": 175.568,
                                "byte_start": 783996,
                                "byte_stop": 787653,
                                "text": "We disagree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.568,
                                "stop": 186.234,
                                "byte_start": 787653,
                                "byte_stop": 830389,
                                "text": "Under the Bankruptcy Code, debt is defined to mean liability on a claim and claim in turn is defined to include any right to payment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 186.234,
                                "stop": 193.042,
                                "byte_start": 830389,
                                "byte_stop": 857557,
                                "text": "In short, a debt is a debt even when the obligation to pay it is also a regulatory condition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.042,
                                "stop": 206.72,
                                "byte_start": 857557,
                                "byte_stop": 912309,
                                "text": "Petitioners also argued that respondent\u2019s obligations are not dischargeable in bankruptcy because it is beyond the authority of Bankruptcy Courts to alter or modify regulatory obligations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 206.72,
                                "stop": 212.196,
                                "byte_start": 912309,
                                "byte_stop": 934252,
                                "text": "Dischargeability however is not tied to the existence of such authority."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.196,
                                "stop": 218.369,
                                "byte_start": 934252,
                                "byte_stop": 958912,
                                "text": "A preconfirmation debt is dischargeable unless it falls within an expressed exception."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 218.369,
                                "stop": 231.713,
                                "byte_start": 958912,
                                "byte_stop": 1012306,
                                "text": "Artistically symmetrical with petitioner\u2019s contention that the Bankruptcy Court has no power to alter regulatory obligations is their contention that the D.C. Circuit has no power to modify or discharge a debt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 231.713,
                                "stop": 243.627,
                                "byte_start": 1012306,
                                "byte_stop": 1059953,
                                "text": "Just as the former is irrelevant to whether the Bankruptcy Court can discharge a debt, so also the latter is irrelevant to order the D.C. Circuit can set aside agency action that violates law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.627,
                                "stop": 251.943,
                                "byte_start": 1059953,
                                "byte_stop": 1093181,
                                "text": "The court did not seek to modify or discharge the debt but merely prevented the FCC from violating Section 525."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 251.943,
                                "stop": 260.279,
                                "byte_start": 1093181,
                                "byte_stop": 1126513,
                                "text": "Finally we reject the contention that our interpretation of Section 525 creates a conflict with the Communications Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 260.279,
                                "stop": 273.429,
                                "byte_start": 1126513,
                                "byte_stop": 1179176,
                                "text": "It does not obstruct the functioning of the Spectrum Auction Provisions since nothing in those provisions demands that cancellation be the sanction for failure to make agreed upon periodic payments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 273.429,
                                "stop": 279.835,
                                "byte_start": 1179176,
                                "byte_stop": 1204776,
                                "text": "Indeed, nothing in those provisions even requires the Commission to permit payment to be made over time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 279.835,
                                "stop": 300.631,
                                "byte_start": 1204776,
                                "byte_stop": 1287950,
                                "text": "What petitioners described as a conflict boils down to nothing more than a policy preference on the FCC\u0027s part for one, selling licenses on credit, and two, canceling licenses rather than asserting security interests in licenses when there is a default."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 300.631,
                                "stop": 307.556,
                                "byte_start": 1287950,
                                "byte_stop": 1315640,
                                "text": "Such administrative preferences cannot be the bases for denying respondent rights provided by the plain terms of law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 307.556,
                                "stop": 320.567,
                                "byte_start": 1315640,
                                "byte_stop": 1367676,
                                "text": "While the FCC retains security interest in these cases, it did not seek to enforce those security interests but opted to eliminate the licenses to the forbidden regulatory step of revoking them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 320.567,
                                "stop": 329.667,
                                "byte_start": 1367676,
                                "byte_stop": 1404143,
                                "text": "The question whether Section 525 would also prevent the Government\u2019s enforcement of its security interests is neither presented nor answered today."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 329.667,
                                "stop": 344.529,
                                "byte_start": 1404143,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion is joined by all Justices except as to Part 3 Justice Stevens who has filed a concurring opinion, and as to the entire opinion and judgment, Justice Breyer who has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
